benoic
------------------------------------------
Benoic implements an interface to control multiple types of house automation
devices. To add a new device type, you have to create a library with the
proper functions, then place the library in the folder specified by
modules_path in your configuration file, then restart the program.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.6.9-1
  libconfig15-1.8.2-1bl1
  libhoel1.4-1.4.29-1bl2
  libjansson4-2.13.1-1
  liborcania2.3-2.3.3-1bl2
  libulfius2.7-2.7.15-1bl2
  libyder1.4-1.4.20-1bl2

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.46.1-1
  cygport-0.37.7-1
  gcc-core-13.4.0-1
  gcc-g++-13.4.0-1
  libconfig-devel-1.8.2-1bl1
  libhoel-devel-1.4.29-1bl2
  libjansson-devel-2.13.1-1
  liborcania-devel-2.3.3-1bl2
  libulfius-devel-2.7.15-1bl2
  libyder-devel-1.4.20-1bl2
  make-4.4.1-2

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/babelouest/benoic

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/babelouest/benoic/archive/refs/tags/v2.1.0.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack benoic-2.1.0-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./benoic-2.1.0-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/benoic-2.1.0-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/benoic-2.1.0-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(benoic)
  /usr/bin/benoic-standalone.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/benoic.README
  /usr/share/doc/benoic/LICENSE
  /usr/share/doc/benoic/README.md

